6 Public Records Law, R.S. 44:1 et seq.
7 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the task force shall submit a written report of
8 findings, conclusions, and recommendations to the Louisiana legislature, the office of the
9 governor, and the office of the attorney general no later than February 1, 2027.
10 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the task force shall terminate following the
11 conclusion of its business or February 1, 2027, whichever occurs first.
12 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that a copy of this Resolution be transmitted to the
13 governor, the attorney general, the director of AARP Louisiana, the executive director of the
14 Louisiana Sheriffs' Association, the president of the Better Business Bureau of South Central
15 Louisiana, the special agent in charge of the New Orleans field office of the Federal Bureau
16 of Investigation, the United States Attorney for the Western District of Louisiana, the United
17 States Attorney for the Middle District of Louisiana, the United States Attorney for the
18 Eastern District of Louisiana, the commissioner of the office of financial institutions, the
19 executive director of the Louisiana Association of Chiefs of Police, the chairman of the
20 Louisiana Bankers Association, and the executive director of the office of elderly affairs.
